parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure (Rod Bearing Failure, Oil Leaks, and Seizure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause a fire.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud knocking or clacking noise
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the oil pressure indicator comes on
the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
